cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY. 

The paper describes a mobile manipulation robot capable of autonomously solving a valve manipulation task using a wrench tool detected, grasped, and finally employed to turn a valve stem. This involves the use of 3D laser scans, object detection architecture based on deep neural networks, and parametrized motion primitives. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep neural networks also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category. Finally, the application of these techniques to achieve autonomous operation of the robot suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible category.
